<caption> <link target-id="element-873" strength="3"/> (magnitude and phase spectra of the highpass FIR filter)  </caption></figure><figure id="element-941"><media id="id1634167" alt=""><image src="../../media/hv41.jpg" mime-type="image/jpeg" height="369" width="467"/></media>
<caption> <link target-id="element-155" strength="3"/> (magnitude and phase spectra of the lowpass IIR filter) </caption></figure><example id="element-155"><para id="element-362">Given the difference equation of a filter as
<m:math display="block">
 <m:semantics>
  <m:mrow>
   <m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mn>1.77</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1.19</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>0.28</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>3</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>0.14</m:mn><m:mi>y</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>n</m:mi><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>2</m:mn><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo>
  </m:mrow>
 <m:annotation encoding="MathType-MTEF">
 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@5C5B@</m:annotation>
 </m:semantics>
</m:math>
</para><para id="element-128">Find its magnitude and phase frequency spectrum.</para>
</example>
      
      
      
      <para id="id6504343"><term> Solution </term></para>
      <para id="id6504347">Notice that the filter is IIR of third order. From the difference equation we can write directly the frequency response:</para>
      <para id="id6094476"><m:math display="block">
 <m:semantics>
  <m:mrow>
   <m:mi>H</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">(</m:mo><m:mi>ω</m:mi><m:mo stretchy="false">)</m:mo><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mfrac>
    <m:mrow>
     <m:mn>0.14</m:mn><m:msup>
      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mi>ω</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
     </m:msup>
     
    </m:mrow>
    <m:mrow>
     <m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>1.77</m:mn><m:msup>
      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mi>ω</m:mi>
      </m:mrow>
     </m:msup>
     <m:mo>+</m:mo><m:mn>1.19</m:mn><m:msup>
      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mi>ω</m:mi><m:mn>2</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
     </m:msup>
     <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mn>0.28</m:mn><m:msup>
      <m:mi>e</m:mi>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mo>−</m:mo><m:mi>j</m:mi><m:mi>ω</m:mi><m:mn>3</m:mn>
      </m:mrow>
     </m:msup>
     
    </m:mrow>
   </m:mfrac>
   
  </m:mrow>
 <m:annotation encoding="MathType-MTEF">
 MathType@MTEF@5@5@@5F61@</m:annotation>
 </m:semantics>
</m:math>
</para>
      <para id="id5535257">Matlab gives the magnitude and phase spectra depicted in <link target-id="element-941" strength="3"/>. Notice that with just a few terns the IIR gives a rather good smooth magnitude spectrum (refer to previous example of FIR filter).</para>
      <example id="element-756"><para id="element-108">The following is the equation of a notch filter:
<m:math display="block">
